title.narrative: Halting the spread of HIV and reducing TB Prevalence and Mortality in Eswatini

description.narrative: Eswatini - TB/HIV - National Emergency Response Council on HIV and AIDS - NERCHA. This program has the following goals: The goal of the HIV NSF 2018-2023 is to super-fast track the HIV response to reduce new HIV infections by 85% and AIDS related mortality by 50% from 2017 levels by 2023.. The goal of the TB NSP 2020-2023 is to reduce TB incidence by 50% and TB deaths by 75% from 2015 baseline by 2023.. The objectives of this program are: HIV: Reduction of HIV incidence among persons aged 15-49 years by 85% by 2023 from the 2017 baselines. HIV: Reduction of HIV incidence among persons aged 15-24 by 85% by 2023 from the 2017 baselines. HIV: Reduction of new HIV infections among infants aged 0-1 year to less than 0.05% by 2023 from 2.5% in 2019. HIV: Reduction of AIDS deaths by 50% by 2023 from the 2017 baselines. TB: Establish and Operationalize Multi-sectoral mechanisms to address TB issues, by 2023. TB: Secure 90% of required TB NSP funding, build capacity and maintain focused positions for TB control at all levels, by 2023. TB: Increase TB treatment coverage (all forms) from 80% in 2018 to 90 % in 2023. TB: Increase the proportion of childhood TB case notifications from 6% in 2019 to 12 % in 2023. TB: Increase TB Preventive Therapy (TPT) uptake from 62% among the under 5 years children TB contacts and from 65% among PLHIV (2019) to 90% by 2023. TB: Increase treatment success rate for all forms of TB (drug-susceptible TB and Drug resistant TB) from 83% in 2019 to 90% in 2023 and 95% in 2025. TB: Reduce the proportion of affected families facing catastrophic costs due to TB to zero by 2023. TB: Increase TB/HIV/NCDs collaborative activities (Diabetes, Hypertension, Chronic lung diseases and Mental Health services) in TB BMUs from unknown in 2019 to 50% BMUs in 2023

title.narrative: Coverage / Output indicator for SWZ-C-NERCHA
Percentage of HIV-positive women who received ART during pregnancy and/or labour and delivery
Percentage of consignments delivered on-time and in-full among the total number of consignments expected to be delivered for the three diseases during the reporting period
Percentage of people on ART among all people living with HIV at the end of the reporting period
Percentage of people living with HIV and on ART, who have a suppressed viral load at 12 months (<1000 copies/ml)
Percentage of people living with HIV initiated on ART who are screened for TB in HIV treatment settings
Number of people who were tested for HIV and received their results during the reporting period

Treatment success rate- all forms: Percentage of TB cases, all forms, bacteriologically confirmed plus clinically diagnosed, successfully treated (cured plus treatment completed) among all TB cases registered for treatment during a specified period, new and relapse cases
Percentage of people living with HIV newly initiated on ART who were screened for TB
Percentage of people living with HIV currently receiving antiretroviral therapy
Number of medical male circumcisions performed according to national standards
Number of notified cases of all forms of TB (i.e. bacteriologically confirmed + clinically diagnosed), new and relapse cases
Percentage of facilities which record and submit data using the electronic information system
Percentage of cases with RR-TB and/or MDR-TB started on treatment for MDR-TB who were lost to follow up during the first six months of treatment
Number of TB cases with RR-TB and/or MDR-TB notified
Percentage of people newly diagnosed with HIV initiated on ART
Percentage of HIV-positive results among the total HIV tests performed during the reporting period
Percentage of registered new and relapse TB patients with documented HIV status
Percentage of HIV-positive new and relapse TB patients on ART during TB treatment
Percentage of PLHIV on ART who initiated TB preventive therapy among those eligible during the reporting period
Number of cases with RR-TB and/or MDR-TB that began second-line treatment
Percentage of HIV-exposed infants receiving a virological test for HIV within 2 months of birth
Percentage of ART sites that had a stock-out of any antiretroviral drugs during the reporting period
Percentage of health facilities with tracer medicines for the three diseases available on the day of the visit or day of reporting
Percentage of pregnant women who know their HIV status
Impact indicator for SWZ-C-NERCHA
Number of new HIV infections per 1000 uninfected population
Percentage of people living with HIV
TB mortality rate per 100,000 population
Number of AIDS-related deaths per 100,000 population
Estimated percentage of children newly infected with HIV from mother-to-child transmission among women living with HIV delivering in the past 12 months
RR-TB and/or MDR-TB prevalence among new TB patients: Proportion of new TB cases with RR-TB and/or MDR-TB
Percentage of men who have sex with men who are living with HIV
TB incidence rate per 100,000 population
Percentage of sex workers who are living with HIV
TB/HIV mortality rate per 100,000 population
Outcome indicator for SWZ-C-NERCHA
Percentage of people living with HIV and on ART who are virologically suppressed
Treatment success rate of all forms of TB - bacteriologically confirmed plus clinically diagnosed, new and relapse cases
Case notification rate of all forms of TB per 100,000 population - bacteriologically confirmed plus clinically diagnosed, new and relapse cases

TB treatment coverage: Percentage of new and relapse cases that were notified and treated among the estimated number of incident TB cases in the same year (all form of TB - bacteriologically confirmed plus clinically diagnosed)
Percentage of people living with HIV who know their HIV status at the end of the reporting period
Percentage of women and men aged 15–49 who report discriminatory attitudes towards people living with HIV
Percentage of (estimated) people living with HIV who have been tested HIV-positive
Notification of RR-TB and/or MDR-TB cases – Percentage of notified cases of bacteriologically confirmed, drug resistant RR-TB and/or MDR-TB as a proportion of all estimated RR-TB and/or MDR-TB cases
Treatment success rate of RR TB and/or MDR-TB: Percentage of cases with RR and/or MDR-TB successfully treated
Percentage of adults and children with HIV, known to be on treatment 12 months after initiation of antiretroviral therapy
